parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To kindle, light. A primary verb; properly, to fasten to, i.e. to set on fire.
A lamp. From the base of leukos; a portable lamp or other illuminator.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To put, place, lay, set, fix, establish. A prolonged form of a primary theo to place.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
A cellar, vault, hidden place, crypt. Feminine of kruptos; a hidden place, i.e. Cellar.
Neither, nor, not even, and not. From ou and de; not however, i.e. Neither, nor, not even.
A primary preposition; under, i.e. of place, or with verbs; of place (underneath) or where (below) or time (when).
A dry measure, nearly two English gallons. Of Latin origin; a modius, i.e. Certain measure for things dry.
But, except, however. Neuter plural of allos; properly, other things, i.e. contrariwise.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
A lamp-stand. From luchnos; a lamp-stand.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To journey in(to), I go in(to), enter, intervene. From eis and poreuomai; to enter.

parse: Verb - Present Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: (primarily physical), I look, see, perceive, discern. A primary verb; to look at.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Brightness, light, splendor, radiance. Probably akin to the base of phos; brilliancy.
